description:
&lt;p&gt;Clinical Lead Boston/Grantham Mental Health Liaison Service Band 7&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based at Boston MHLS, Dept. of Psychiatry, Pilgrim Hospital, Boston. Lincolnshire PE21 9QS, however, providing Clinical and Managerial support to MHLS staff working in the Grantham Urgent Treatment Centre.&lt;br /&gt;Hours: Full-time 37.50 Hours per week to be worked over a 24 hour shift period.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We seek to appoint an enthusiastic and dynamic Clinical Lead who is passionate about caring for and meeting the needs of Patients in the Acute Trust settings of Pilgrim Hospital, Boston and Grantham Urgent Treatment Centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Clinical Lead will fulfil a clinical nurse role which includes rapid access and biopsychosocial assessment of Patients over the age of 16 years, presenting with and without medical co-morbidities. The Boston Mental health Liaison Service is supported by a Service manager, and 3 Consultant Psychiatrists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A key purpose of the post is to improve patient experience, providing a rapid and appropriate response, and agreeing a safe and effective plan of care based on clinical need and an accurate assessment of presenting risks. The post holder will be competent and confident in positive risk taking and will support junior staff to develop skills in positive risk taking that will promote patient autonomy and avoid admissions which are not supported by clinical need. You will provide senior presence, expert advice and support the other members of the multidisciplinary team. The post holder will also provide coordination, clinical supervision, Managerial Supervision and Appraisal in order support to all staff on their shift. You will be an active member in the on-going service design and development.The post holder will provide increase senior clinical and managerial cover to this team by taking responsibility for the operational management of the shift and other overall team operational tasks and performance monitoring. Be able to problem solve and enhance professional development of the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is suitable for a Registered Mental Health Nurse or Registered Learning Disability Nurse/Occupational Therapist/Social Worker with recent experience in Mental Health Liaison and crisis mental health setting at a band 6 or above. You should enjoy working within a busy and challenging environment, and must be able to work effectively under pressure. You will have a sound knowledge of mental illness and therapeutic interventions and competence in mental health assessment and treatment formulation to achieve positive outcomes for our clients. You will be creative and innovative in your approach, and will work collaboratively with patients and their carers in the formulation of care and crisis plans. Your communication skills will be well developed and you will be able to effectively liaise with other mental health teams and third sector providers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Staff are highly valued by the management team and are actively encouraged and supported in their professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
